				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Usually in the morning, while I'm sipping coffee, I enjoy a nice & relaxing solo stroll through PoI.  The zone is usually empty at that time and the AA exp does add up.
<br />

<br />
Never seems to fail...  A lvl 46-51 or so toon will zone in.  If they are usually quiet and don't bug me, sometimes I invite them for some free exp.  But sometimes I just wanna be left alone.  That gets the ball rolling.  Whenever in one of those moods, I always seem to get a tell from one of the low levels if they could group with me.
<br />

<br />
I will tell them that I'm just soloing before work and will be logging soon.  Then I get something like them telling me how great their gear is and how they will help speed up my exp.  I advise them that actually they will slow me down (gotta make sure they stay alive = spending mana on heals) or such.  Then they get pissy, calling me a zone hog, stingy, etc.
<br />

<br />
I guess what I'm trying to say is...  If you log into PoI in the a.m., see old churizo drinking some joe (hands shaking from the jitters), don't bug me for a plvl)
<br />

<br />
 <img src="images/smiles/eusa_dance.gif" alt="Dancing" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Thanks for the ear.<br />_________________<br />Churizo Andeggs
<br />
65 Leezard Beastlord
